╗in Loving and lasting memory of my precious angel
BALAZS MIKLOS TOTH
(7.1.1985 27.11 2013)
He loved Battersea Park
As did his mother Zsuzsanna (d31.12.2011)
Gordon"Ё
╟Stranger Stop Here and Rest Your Thoughts on
LOVELY LISA GRAYLEY
Mum to Pretty Lottie, Sweetheart to Paul and Beautiful Friend to
Those of Us Who Knew Her "Sweet Dreams Sis""╥
╢In Loving Memory of
Victor & Zillah Moisan 
Love Derrick, Margaret, Steve,
Chris, Holly & Beth
xxxxx

'When someone you love becomes
a memory the memory becomes a
treasure'"╧
╤THOMAS BRAWLEY 03/08/1919 to 31/12/2009
Beloved husband, father & grandfather. Tommy liked to walk daily
round the Park to observe the seasonal changes unfolding.
We enjoyed many happy family hours in his special place.
A wonderful husband and father with great wit and intelligence
he loved his family dearly and we miss him so much.
AGNES BRAWLEY
20th September 1923 to 22nd of March 2013
Much loved Wife, Mother and Grandmother"╫
╨In memory of
Derek Lane
From a select number of friends who spent many happy
hours in his company and together enjoyed the splendour
of this city and the tranquility of these gardens"╬
